bcl:definition.bcl:text:
assessment record means the record produced by an independent automated
refraction conducted by a person who is authorized under the Act to conduct independent
automated refractions;

contact lens means a lens or mold designed or offered for the purposes
of being placed on the surface of the cornea or other anterior surface of an eye to
correct the refractive error of, or induce physiological change in, the eye;

interpupillary distance means one or more measurements of the distance
between the pupils of the eyes, as will be required for the proper fitting of
eyeglasses;

prescription means the record of an authorization to dispense a vision
appliance for use by a named individual but does not include an assessment record or a
contact lens record;

bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
plus or minus 2.00 dioptres in either eye since the date of the most recent
              prescription or assessment record, if any, provided by the client to the
              registrant;
